# Public routes vs login-by-default

- **Unauthenticated (public) pages** belong **only** under `app/public_app` (URLs, entrypoints, templates for those flows). Mark their views with `login_not_required` so `LoginRequiredMiddleware` does not redirect guests.
- **Everything else** is treated as **authenticated-only** by `LoginRequiredMiddleware` — do not add parallel “public” routes outside `public_app` unless there is an exceptional, documented reason.
